name: London at Quarter to One
description:
Composite panorama of the view over the City of London with Blackfriars Bridge and Station crossing the River Thames on the left. // February 28th 2018 was a (very) rare snowy day for London. If you look closely, you can see the time on the clock tower of St Paul's Cathedral (top middle) and other insights into a memorable Tuesday afternoon for the city. // Fuji X-T20 50mm f/1.8
